    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Due to the changes, now we can pass string values to the `refine` function. This allow the user to implement a range widget without caring about parsing the numbers from the rendering.\r\n\r\nBut since the signature of the `refine` function is `(Array<number,number>) => void` we should probably only handle numbers and empty values (the later is used to be able to reset the range).\r\n\r\nWDYT?",
