    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Due to the changes, now we can pass string values to the refine function. This allow the user to implement a range widget without caring about parsing the numbers from the rendering.\r\n\r\nThat's nice and it makes in terms of usage. What is preventing us from supporting both numbers, null and strings? I'm not sure it's consistent with other refine API's that takes numbers as parameters 🤔 but that would be a win in terms of usability.",
